 |__| |__|_.__/\___/\_,_|\__|                         @{b}(c) GREMLiNS MAXsWARE@{ub}

 In brief, FOR_SALE is an advert type door allowing users to leave for sale
 adverts, and wanted adverts. This is another great Door for MAXs BBS/Pro.

 Version: 2.2  [update from version 2.1 - re-release]

 I got bored, and just to let people know I'm still alive... just. ;-)

@endnode
@node 2 " For Sale Guide (c)97-00 Glen Martin of GREMLiNS BBS "
@prev 1
@next 4
@{"°°" link 4}
  _____         _        _ _
 |_   _|_ _  __| |_ __ _| | |
  |   || ' \(_-<  _/ _` | | |
 |_____|_||_/__/\__\__,_|_|_|                         @{b}(c) GREMLiNS MAXsWARE@{ub}

 Firstly, if you haven't already  (..regarding other doors by me), create a
 directory called "gremlins" in your Doors: directory. You must assign this
 new directory in your startup-sequence, so just do it Mr SysOp.

 Eg: "assign gremlins: doors:gremlins/"

 Unpack the FOR_SALE archive into this gremlins directory and run via MAXs.

 Eg: (using function 34) gremlins:for_sale/for_sale

 Simply run the Door,  using MAXs run door function [34], and test the Door
 for yaself, etc.  Users are allowed to leave an advert,  etc, view it, and
 download the  adverts, and more.  The only work  to be done on the SysOp's
 behalf is maintaining the advert lists, etc.  Wow! Too hard for sum, thou!
 You can alter watever screen files,  where necessary and  change the text,
 etc, where possible. [grin]

 There is now a SysOp's  menu wich is accessed  via `Alt+Shift+S'  keys and
 can be accessed by  users who have their  name in the  `FOR_SALE.sysopaxs'
 list.  The SysOp  menu enables editing  of the text/list files created and
 nutting more. To use this menu and features, you require CED (text editor)
 in your C: directory.

 Also  if there  are any users  who you want  to keep out  of the  Door for
 watever reasons,  you can  enter the users name in the `FOR_SALE.badusers'
 list.

@endnode
